snippet.textDisplay:
Oooooh! Stow stopper performance! Hat's Up!!!! To the Rapper! To Arnob and Sumi, everyone simply sounded mind blowing, but there is a chance that this score might in the long run end up loosing its gimmick and coming under stark criticism regarding a very superficial or untrue interpretation of our Baul Spirit, that the original score Bhober Pagol pertained to! In that sense, I might be wrong (I would love to if I prove wrong) this simply would or could fail to do any good justice to the BAUL genre or the link that enrich the tradition, let alone become any sensible fusion or fission,
Coke studio Bangla has shown already a bigger promise than this, but score like this one or Prarthona we expect could have become more lesser than the shadow reflux of so called few wind of change trash item people have already discarded in distaste! I know even achieving something like this is still challenging, but not impossible to overcome the backlash it awaits for not giving the right treatment a song, specially that are one of the soulful cores of Bangla music which makes us totally different from other genres as well! A song that should have been soulful rather than hurting its true colour and existence is no way be any bench mark for the platform like COKE studio.
